 "awd_abstract_narration": "9708915  This research focuses on applying formal methods to the problem  of certification of imported software. Formal systems such as set  constraints, Kleene algebra and Kleene algebra with tests, and  the modal mu-calculus have been shown to provide potent tools for  practical program analysis and verification. It is proposed to  develop these systems further with special focus on efficient  practical algorithms and to investigate their use as tools for  software certification. The goals are (i) to make it easy for a  software vendor to construct a certificate to be downloaded along  with a compiled object that ensures that certain safety  conditions are met; and (ii) to make it easy for a client to  check the certificate to verify that the foreign code is safe to  run locally. It is hoped that this work will contribute to the  elimination of untrustworthy software.  ***",
